        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ci): smooth PR runner-registration bursts",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- skip the CI matrix when a pull request's newest head commit is empty, while keeping the lightweight preflight/security path\n- cap the large Linux test matrix at 6 concurrent jobs and smaller contract/platform waves at 2-4\n- add workflow guard coverage for both controls\n\n## Why\n\nBlacksmith reported GitHub secondary rate limiting on runner registration: repeated agentic re-trigger commits and many simultaneous roughly-100-job PR matrices create registration bursts above the org ceiling. The CI workflow already cancels superseded runs per PR, but it still admitted every empty re-trigger commit and allowed every matrix entry to register at once.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- YAML/workflow guard assertions via the repository's `yaml` parser\n- structured autoreview, Codex engine: clean with no accepted/actionable findings\n\nThe normal pnpm test command could not run in the temporary worktree because pnpm attempted dependency reconciliation; no install was performed.\n",
